---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getCopy } from '../../data/site';

const language = 'fr';
const copy = getCopy(language);
---

<BaseLayout title={`${copy.pages.about.title} - ${copy.name}`} description={copy.description} language={language} path="/about/">
	<main class="about-page">
		<a class="case-back about-back" href="/fr/">
			<span aria-hidden="true"></span>
			Back home
		</a>

		<section class="about-hero">
			<h1><em>How</em> I got here?</h1>
			<div class="about-story">
				<p class="about-story-note">oh no, she's going to write a wall of text about her life</p>
				<p>
					Back in the early 2000s, I was four and
					completely absorbed by my dad's computer. It felt like freedom: this strange machine could teach me
					almost anything, if I was curious enough to ask.
				</p>
				<p>
					I later followed the classic science path: a scientific high school diploma with a mathematics focus, a
					computer science bachelor degree in France, and a master's in computer science and AI at the University of Montreal (before it became that famous I swear).
				</p>
				<p>
					Starting that early probably explains why I now care so much about the impact of technology on society,
					and why I try to build with more intention.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<aside class="about-random">
			<p class="case-kicker">Random facts</p>
			<p>
				I formatted my first laptop around age 12 after corrupting my mother's Windows installation and deciding it
				was better if nobody noticed. I started making simple HTML websites around 13.
			</p>
			<p>
				I also have an artistic side: I like writing poetry, and I followed a few acting classes.
			</p>
		</aside>

		<section class="about-skills">
			<p class="case-kicker">Technical Skills</p>
			<div>
				<h2>I do a lot.</h2>
				<p>
					I think of myself as a generalist with a wide technical range: OOP languages like C++, C#, and Java;
					web tools like React, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, PHP, and Flask; Python for data and automation; and even
					functional languages like Scheme.
				</p>
				<p>
					I build web platforms, XR experiences, games, design systems, data tools, experimental tasks, and
					scientific papers. I like moving between disciplines and making the pieces talk to each other.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<a class="about-play-link" href="/fr/play">
			Play
			<span aria-hidden="true"></span>
		</a>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
